Pre-Game Insights: Turkey will be without key player Hakan Calhanoglu for their last-16 contest against Austria at this summer's European Championship.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Calhanoglu sent Turkey ahead in the 50th minute of the clash with a rasping strike.
Calhanoglu will be suspended against Austria on Tuesday, having been booked for remonstrating with the referee after the Czech Republic goal.
Turkey picked up six points from their three games in Group F to finish second behind Portugal.
